5:
Ah. You're here to pick up some
materials? Take as much as you
need. There's plenty more where this
came from.
9:
I heard there was something else
you needed help with. What is it?
12: Yes. I'd like to interview everyone, too.
19:
Ah, I see. Gathering data for a book
chronicling your journey, eh? Not a
bad idea...
23:
I plan on researching the undead to
unlock the secret of Regitare's
immortality. The possibilities would
be—quite literally—endless.
27:
As for me, I plan on continuing my
research into elemental recycling.
Considering the future applications,
it was the only logical choice.
31:
How about you, Estel? And you,
Regitare?
36:
Not much will change, but nothing is
set in stone. I suppose I shall
accompany the King of Man on her
next journey once she leaves this
world.
39:
Hahaha! Funny for ye to ask
someone this long dead about his
plans for the future! I suppose these
old bones are best off protecting the
forest.
44:
But Lord Regitare, is that truly what
you wish to do?
47:
The Garden of the Sprites will never
be the same... That much is certain.
And it will only continue to change
from here on out.
52:
Right you are, lad. The sprites will
disappear, most likely. But that's fine.
Challua and Shroombo said it
themselves.
57:
"Fine," you say? It sure doesn't sound
fine...
61:
On a grander time scale of centuries
and millennia, we must all learn to
say our goodbyes. The forest
dwellers know this to be true.
64:
But the children of the forest vowed
to live in the moment and enjoy
their time together. Just look at
them... They're 'aving a blast!
76:
Lilith, Challua... I'd like to interview
you about your plans for the future.
80:
My path forward is clear. I must
create a peaceful kingdom for my
people to call home.
84:
But this time, my words are more
than just empty bravado. I must
stay strong for them. And I will not
stop until my mission is complete.
86:
However, my migration plan doesn't
end here. My ambitions extend to
other worlds as well. But then again,
I do have the tendency to bite off
more than I can chew.
91:
Challua wants to do lots and lots,
too! Fun things! Like play with
everyone... and decorate tree for
holidays!
93:
But there's one thing Challua wants
most of all!
96:
Challua wants to become a cherry
blossom.
104:
Everyone says Shibuya's cherry
blossoms, sooo pretty! Challua will
blossom, too!
110:
I'm still shocked that's even within
the realm of possibility for you... Are
you really able to change forms like
that?
114:
Challua is child of forest,
remember? Anything possible!
119:
You two have really come to be
good friends.
124:
Hehe, that we have. And though
there are still many hardships we
must endure throughout our journey
to come...
126:
I believe in us. Within each of us
dwells the power to overcome
whatever obstacles we might face.
131:
Thank you both for sharing your
dreams.
135:
That's why you still have a future as
a leader, Alk. Even if you can no
longer fight.
138:
You always have a seat at my
council, if you so desire.
143:
I appreciate the offer, but
government isn't really for me.
Making decisions for myself is one
thing, but for an entire world?
149:
Hm... Very well, then. I shan't pry
further into your reasons.
152:
I was hoping you would join, as you
have a particular set of skills that
would be of use. But I shall have to
make do.
155:
You see, Mayor Takamori
approached me with an interesting
proposal. He has invited children
from the kingdom to Shibuya's new
school for a cultural exchange
program.
159:
Which means you'll be seeing a lot
more of us soon.
165:
Hee hee! We can go to school
together, Light!
171:
Ngh... How many times must I repeat
myself—I am a fully grown man!
176:
It will be a while before any schools
open in this world. So please... look
after the little ones for me.
191:
Oh, and we're not the only world
who received the offer.
198:
Right, right! The Shibuya exchange
program. Totally! Word gets around
fast, y'know.
201:
We're planning on sending Teo and
some of the other talented young
beastfolk to participate.
205:
As such, we'll be counting on you to
take care of our kin. Our next
generation is in your hands.
209:
And what's with the secret plan to
bail on us, bro? You can't just up and
leave us like this!
212:
Yeah, yeah... Half of the reason
you're upset is 'cause you won't be
able to boss around old Whitetail
anymore.
216:
Uh, rude? That's only, like, a third of
the reason!
220:
No need to be so dramatic, Claw.
This isn't goodbye for good. Do
come back and visit us when you
can, Nimbus.
224:
True, true... At least stop by for New
Year's and bring us some good luck.
227:
If it'll get you to shut your trap, I'll
think about it.
232:
Don't worry, bro. We'll keep the fort
down and make sure these little
guys have a bright future to look
forward to.
235:
So, yeah. Something like that. Did
that answer your question?
239: Yes. Thank you for your help.
244: So, how are the interviews going?
251:
But I'm not finished yet. I want to
hear more about everyone's dreams
for the future.
